Description.Name: Run Cheatah Run
Description.Details: You sit in your command chair, nursing a cup of coffee while staring at the Console, the feeling of this scenario having played over and over again multiple times flitting through your head, "I'm beginning to question whether the benefits of faster travel times by using Pirate Points is worth it." Dr Murad has the panel to the Console open again, playing around with the Cheatah Nav Computer. She leans back from her work and looks over to you, "I've tried everything I can Commander, but I think our only option is to just replace the Cheatah Nav Computer and see if the sound goes away." Your head pounding from the random banging resounding out of the Console makes it hard to think clearly, "So we just yank out a potentially good part in the hopes it fixes the issue? Sounds expensive." Dr Murad stops work on the Console, "After labour from the astechs as well as other bits and pieces, it should not be more than ¢400,000 C-Bills." You moan, "Ugh, more expenses. Can we at least sell or reuse it?" Dr Murad shakes her head, "No Commander. The way these pirates have cobbled this device together basically means you have to literally destroy the part to replace it. So I can either try replacing the Cheatah Nav Computer or we can ignore it and hope it goes away on its own."

Description.Name: Replace the Cheatah Nav Computer
Description.Details: Replace Part

Description.Name: Replace Cheatah Nav Computer
Description.Details:
You rub your temples for a moment, "Go ahead and change out the Cheatah Nav Computer."

Dr Murad nods and instructs her team of astechs to begin the process of swapping out the Cheatah Nav Computer.

Description.Name: If it's not broke...
Description.Details: Live with the Noise

Description.Name: Live with the Noise
Description.Details:
You rub your temples for a moment, "I just cannot see the logic in blindly replacing a possibly good part.  We've dealt with this random knocking noise so far.  At least it's not happening all the time."

Dr Murad nods and instructs her team of astechs to begin to reassemble the panels of the Console.  As they work, she turns back to you, "I'll let you know when whichver faulty component finally fails and takes the Console fully offline."
